cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.SOC, cs.DS, cs.GT 

This paper focuses on identifying community structures in dynamic networks, which involves analyzing social networks that are constantly changing in membership. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including social and information networks (cs.SI), systems and control (cs.SD), social and economic networks (cs.SOC), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and game theory (cs.GT). Given the emphasis on social networks and community detection, cs.SI and cs.SOC are the most likely sub-categories. However, the use of game theoretic approaches and the focus on dynamic networks also make cs.GT and cs.SD relevant. Finally, the use of algorithms and data structures to analyze network data suggests that cs.DS is a possible sub-category as well.
